1 transfer or sale of the district's real or personal property to another governmental or
2 quasi-governmental agency in exchange for money or a similar type of property that
3 equals or exceeds the fair market value of the district property as determined by an
4 independent appraisal conducted by:
5 (a) An individual or organization not affiliated with the district or its officers or
6 employees, using a generally accepted national or professional standard; or
7 (b) A district's officers or employees using a nationally published valuation of
8 property based on the most recent edition of the publication.
